metadata.name: Influence no.3:Auras #48
metadata.description:
The third set of the ‚ÄúInfluence‚Äù series implies the creation of an abstract artwork based on algorithms and colors. Each of the color waves with different orientations next to each other creates an aura state that reminds of abstract acrylic paintings with spatula technique. Various densities and more than 12 color palettes have been used.

-----------

- Add &density=2 to 8 to the live view URL to render the image at higher resolution.

- Press ‚Äôs‚Äô on the live mode to save the artwork.

note:
I highly recommend that you make sure you have enough RAM space and use the Chrome browser or Opera to view the animation in the best possible way. Rendering may take several minutes due to the high density of the artwork.

Made with p5js.

metadata.name: contrapuntos #289
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodr√≠guez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: Paper Art 3D #96
metadata.description:
Welcome to ‚ÄúPaper Art 3D‚Äù

‚ÄúPaper Art 3D‚Äù is the beginning of my journey as a new generative art creator. Starting from simple geometrical shapes like a small step towards to something greater in the future. 
It all began from simple 3D shapes that combined into mountains, trees, and houses. Then everything expanded and united into many exotic cityscapes. Each with their own style and uniqueness.

Built with three.js.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Space Bar  --> Save a simple screenshot image of the canvas
Mouse: Drag & Scroll  --> Rotate & Zoom in-out 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - -

metadata.name: Ataraxis #432
metadata.description:
Ataraxis (or a broken volume renderer) is an exploration in balancing discomfort and calm. The piece generates spaces on the fly that are designed to elicit strange and uncomfortable feelings - like a desolate, alien dreamscape - claustrophobic, surreal, not quite real yet strangely recognisable. But the idea is that while these spaces feel uncomfortable, they're also strangely, antilogically calming. The idea is to elicit a sanguine emotion, to make the viewer feel calm in a strange place, and to lead them somewhere else.

This work is the culmination of many years of work researching volumetric rendering techniques. This token uses a raymarching technique that is intentionally broken in various ways.

Controls:
Double-click to download
&w=X&h=y to change the size of the piece
&dpr=x to change the resolution of the pice - higher resolutions will result in slightly different artworks as the browser attempts to compensate for the overlarge canvas
&fullscreen=true to change the token to display the full size of your browser. This may impact the rendering of the token, so use with caution
